& [SLMSlice41FixtureExpansionMatrix] is a work-ready slice for the next deterministic fixture set
  + [slice_id] is SLM-41
  + [status] is specification_complete
  + [effort] is S-M
  + [risk] is low
  + [depends_on] is SLM-11, SLM-29, SLM-32
  + [scope] is define fixture sentences for imperative subject, negation, coordination, pronoun reference, and attachment ambiguity
  + [deliverable] is SOP fixture matrix and optional mock-provider fixture expansion
  + [acceptance_criteria] is each fixture has expected workspace, diffusion trace, wobble vector, graph boundary, and primer expectation
  + [proof_route] is SOP review then WSL cargo test when fixtures are implemented
  + [exclusions] is broad natural-language benchmark suite
  + [next_action] is implement selected fixture cases in dependent slices

  ! [CompletionEvidence] is the SLM-41 SOP review record
    @ [contract] is slm_project/specifications/contracts/SLM_Fixture_Expansion_Matrix_Contract.sop
    @ [fixture_count] is 7
    @ [coverage] is imperative subject, negation, coordination, pronoun reference, attachment ambiguity, security veto, and threshold boundary
    @ [proof] source gate remains responsible for file consistency until Rust fixture slices implement the cases
